answers.answer: I did have trace amounts of protein show up in my urin late in pregnancy. Although it was due to other complications that required me to be induced at 36wks.
Gestational diabetes is high levels of sugar (glucose) in urine.Protein in urine would be associated with high blood pressure and pre-eclampsia.
I've had this with both my kids and with as far as you are I would not worry

question: Anyone else have trace protein in their urine late in pregnancy? I'm 39+4. Just worried about developing gestational diabetes very late in pregnancy. Anyone ever here of this?
